We recommended to the Mayor through the Accounting Unit: 

To fully adhere with Section 1 and 1.2 of COA Circular 2012-001;
To strengthen internal control in the granting of Cash Advances to avoid unliquidated Cash advances at year end which shall include but not limited to establishing cash advance cut-offs on December, monitoring those with previously unsettled balances and prohibiting them from drawing new cash advances unless prior CAs are already settled;
To prohibit cash advance settlements on staggered basis, immediate liquidation should be applied whereof; 
To assign personnel who will assist Accounting Office to monitor and exhaust possible means to collect outstanding cash advances from personnel no longer connected to the LGU;
To enforce immediate settlement of unliquidated cash advances. Non-settlement by respective accountable officers will constitute application of Item 9.0 of COA Circular 2012-004.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor thru Inspection unit and accounting office to:
Discontinue the practice of leaving the “Date Received” blank in the Acceptance and Inspection Reports and Delivery Receipts. Indicate the exact date the items, materials or project was/were delivered, accepted and inspected;
Fully adhere to Appendix 50 and 51 of the Government Accounting Manual Volume II for LGUs;
For the accounting unit to carefully examine that supporting documents for payments are complete and proper and impose liquidated damages for delayed deliveries.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor through the BAC and TWG to:
Carefully examine eligibility documents; by cautiously evaluating the legal, technical and financial documents submitted by bidders during preliminary evaluation and post-qualification before recommending the award of the contract; 
Strengthen post qualification procedures and activities in compliance with Rule X of the Revised IRR of RA 9184. This may include but not limited to the following, the Procurement Unit maintaining an updated database/ schedule of contractors and their track records (completed works) with the LGU which shall be readily available during conduct of every post qualification for purposes of verifying outstanding works and;
Impose administrative sanctions/penalties to the contractors/suppliers for the submission of eligibility requirements containing false information or falsified documents.

